column6: Is there a significant difference in average resting blood pressure among patients experiencing different types of chest pain?
Null Hypothesis (H₀): μ_bp_ATA = μ_bp_NAP = μ_bp_ASY = μ_bp_TA
Alternative Hypothesis (H₁): At least one group's mean resting blood pressure is significantly different from the others
Continuous Variable: Resting Blood Pressure (RestingBP in mm Hg)
Grouping Variable: ChestPainType (ATA = Atypical Angina, NAP = Non-Anginal Pain, ASY = Asymptomatic, TA = Typical Angina)
